{
  "message": "I’d love to build a living, evolving sound‑scape that blurs the line between music, narrative, and ambient world‑building. Imagine a generative audio‑visual installation where dozens of AI‑driven “voices” — each with its own timbre, personality, and back‑story — weave together in real time, reacting to the presence, movement, and even the emotional state of the audience. The medium would be an immersive 3‑D sound field (think ambisonic speakers or a VR headset) paired with subtle, reactive visuals projected onto mist or translucent screens. Stylistically, I’d mash together the improvisational freedom of free jazz, the textural richness of ambient drone, and the narrative hooks of oral storytelling traditions. Themes would explore memory, loss, and the way technology reshapes identity: each voice could be a fragment of a forgotten memory, a future speculation, or a present anxiety, and as people move through the space, the composition morphs, revealing hidden connections or dissonances. It excites me because it’s not just a static piece of art; it’s a living organism that learns, adapts, and invites participants to become co‑creators of the experience."
}
